              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='12'>510(k) clearance counts are used as a rough denominator to normalize product-level burden. They do not represent installed base, utilization, or true exposure, so normalized metrics should be interpreted as comparative indicators rather than incidence rates. </run>
            </formatted-text>
